# AI-Driven Zero-Day Exploit Detection and Defense System: Free Resources

This README provides a collection of free online resources to help you study the nature of zero-day vulnerabilities, AI-based methodologies in cybersecurity, and how to define your project scope and objectives.

## 1. Study the Nature of Zero-Day Vulnerabilities

- **[MITRE ATT&CK Framework](https://attack.mitre.org/):**  
  A free, comprehensive database of tactics, techniques, and procedures used in cyber attacks, including zero-day exploits.

- **[OWASP Top Ten](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/):**  
  Provides detailed explanations of various vulnerabilities, including zero-day vulnerabilities.

- **[Exploit Database](https://www.exploit-db.com/):**  
  A free archive of public exploits and vulnerable software, useful for understanding how zero-day vulnerabilities are exploited.

- **[Google Scholar](https://scholar.google.com/):**  
  Search for free academic papers on zero-day vulnerabilities and exploit detection.

## 2. Look into AI-Based Methodologies in Cybersecurity

- **[arXiv.org](https://arxiv.org/):**  
  A repository of free research papers, including those on AI and machine learning in cybersecurity. Search for terms like “AI in cybersecurity” or “anomaly detection.”

- **[KDnuggets](https://www.kdnuggets.com/):**  
  Offers free articles and tutorials on AI, machine learning, and their applications in cybersecurity.

- **[IBM Security Intelligence](https://securityintelligence.com/):**  
  Provides free insights and articles on AI-driven security practices and technologies.

- **[Black Hat on YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/user/BlackHatOfficialYT):**  
  Offers free videos of talks and presentations on cybersecurity, including AI-based methodologies.

## 3. Define Project Scope and Objectives

- **[Coursera - Free Courses](https://www.coursera.org/):**  
  Search for free courses on project management, which include defining project scope and objectives. Courses like "Introduction to Project Management" are often available with free access.

- **[edX - Free Courses](https://www.edx.org/):**  
  Offers free project management and cybersecurity courses that can help you define your project scope and objectives.

- **[Project Management Institute (PMI)](https://www.pmi.org/):**  
  Provides free articles and resources on project management basics, including defining scope and objectives.

- **[GitHub - Open Source Projects](https://github.com/):**  
  Explore open-source projects related to zero-day detection and AI in cybersecurity to see how others have structured their projects.

---

Feel free to explore these resources to gain a solid foundation in zero-day vulnerabilities, AI methodologies in cybersecurity, and project management. Happy learning!
